Specifically, the real data came from the daily report of each country and was collected by Our World in Data [44]. The real data included the number of people who had been tested and the number of people who had tested positive (confirmed cases) every day. Based on the data, the testing-positive rate was calculated. For country i, its testing-positive rate curve reaches the peak Pi on date Ti. We let \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
